DIV2.P:
Here begins the ill Blood that breaks out
as soon as they go off; and from hence
it is that we have nothing so bitter writ∣ten,
and said against the Dissenters as by
such of their young Ministers, who have,
for some Time, been bred, Anglice starv'd,
among them, and have gone off to the
Church, such as M—; N—; R—;
H—; Wessley; Robertson; Hasset; Palmer;
and others.
